; Mini Benchy proxy — exercises same motion patterns as a real 3D Benchy
; but with fewer moves for fast validation. Tests:
; - XY travel moves at various speeds
; - Perimeter-style moves (connected rectangles at print speed)
; - Layer changes (Z moves)
; - Speed changes (travel vs print)
; - Acceleration/deceleration
;
; Expected print time should be calculable from move lengths and speeds.
; Total XY distance at F1200 (20mm/s): ~3200mm → ~160s
; Z moves at F300 (5mm/s): ~50mm → ~10s
; Travel moves at F6000 (100mm/s): ~800mm → ~8s
; Approx total: ~180s

; Startup
SET_KINEMATIC_POSITION X=125 Y=125 Z=125
G1 Z120 F300

; Layer 1 — base rectangle (perimeter)
G1 X50 Y50 F6000
G1 X200 Y50 F1200
G1 X200 Y200 F1200
G1 X50 Y200 F1200
G1 X50 Y50 F1200

; Layer 1 — inner perimeter
G1 X55 Y55 F6000
G1 X195 Y55 F1200
G1 X195 Y195 F1200
G1 X55 Y195 F1200
G1 X55 Y55 F1200

; Layer 2
G1 Z119.8 F300
